    <title>
      On the Convergence of $\mathcal{O}(n^2)$   Algorithms for
      Sparse   Matrix Factorization   with $\epsilon$-Approximation
    </title>
    <summary>
      We study the convergence properties of $O(n^2)$ algorithms
      for sparse   matrix   factorization.  Our analysis shows   that
      the approximation error is bounded by $\epsilon$ under mild
      assumptions on the   input matrix structure.
    </summary>
